      "content": "thanks for that. valgrind might be too heavy for the actual target hardware though, so i'll probably have to stick to manual instrumentation or lighter tools. \n\ncan you expand on point 2? if i see a specific allocation type growing, what's the best way to trace that back to the specific function or object instance that's failing to release it? specifically in a way that doesn't tank the real-time performance of the controller too much.",
